---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Learning Linux From Scratch">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[68ch] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-12 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="flex gap-2 text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono">
        <span>Field Notes</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>May 2026</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-tight">
        Learning Linux From Scratch
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] italic">
        "Master the command line before automating systems operations."
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 text-[#FAFAFA] text-base leading-[1.7] tracking-tight font-normal">
      <p>
        Linux system administration is a cornerstone of backend development and security audits.
        I began learning Linux by forcing myself to operate purely inside CLI terminals.
        Removing visual GUI environments forces you to understand the underlying file structures and permissions models.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        My early logs document process coordination tools (`systemd`, `cron`, `htop`) and user permissions boundaries.
        Understanding how process threads execute, read system inputs, and manage resource limits is essential.
        I also spent time configuring local system firewalls to audit ports and monitor active sockets.
      </p>

      <p>
        The CLI terminal is not a retro interface. It is a precise environment for systems coordination.
        Writing down bash logs and system monitoring routines helps consolidate these foundational skills.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Article Footer -->
    <footer class="flex flex-col gap-8 border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pt-12 mt-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 text-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <h4 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-medium font-mono font-semibold">Related Logs</h4>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2">
            <li>
              <a href="/writing/linux-network-security" class="text-[#2563EB] hover:underline">
                Linux Network Security and Port Monitoring Logs
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
